<div id="outline-container-org0aeb505" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org0aeb505">Unidad 2</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org0aeb505">
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>Complete the sentences with this, that, these, those.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>that</li>
<li>those</li>
<li>this</li>
<li>these / those</li>
<li>that</li>
<li>that</li>
</ol></li>

<li>Rewrite these sentences using possesive pronouns / adjectives.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>His car is in the garage.</li>
<li>These documents are mine.</li>
<li>Their parents are away at the moment.</li>
<li>Its colours are beautiful.</li>
<li>This handbag is hers.</li>
<li>Excuse me, is this passport yours?</li>
</ol></li>

<li>Complete the sentences with personal pronouns.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>them</li>
<li>i   / it</li>
<li>he  / us</li>
<li>us  / they</li>
<li>i   / us</li>
<li>you / them</li>
</ol></li>

<li>Complete the sentences with reflexive pronouns.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>myself</li>
<li>ourselves</li>
<li>themselves</li>
<li>himself</li>
<li>yourself</li>
<li>herself</li>
</ol></li>

<li>Choose the correct answer.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>each other</li>
<li>themselves</li>
<li>one</li>
<li>ones</li>
<li>each other</li>
<li>itself</li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org619bd7c" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org619bd7c">Unit 3</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org619bd7c">
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>Complete this text with a(n) or the.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>a</li>
<li>the</li>
<li>the</li>
<li>the</li>
<li>a</li>
<li>a</li>
<li>the</li>
<li>the</li>
<li>a</li>
<li>a</li>
<li>the</li>
<li>a</li>
<li>an</li>
<li>a</li>
<li>a</li>
<li>the</li>
<li>a</li>
<li>the</li>
<li>the</li>
<li>the</li>
</ol></li>

<li>Complete the sentences with the article the. In some cases, no
article is necessary.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>the / ………</li>
<li>……… / ………</li>
<li>the / ………</li>
<li>………</li>
<li>the / the</li>
<li>……… / the</li>
<li>………</li>
<li>the</li>
</ol></li>

<li>Rewrite these sentences in the singular.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>There is a rose in the garden.</li>
<li>I've got an interesting book.</li>
<li>The cup is on the selve.</li>
<li>The old ladie fell downstairs and broke her leg.</li>
<li>The biggest librarie in town is closed on Sundays.</li>
<li>We need to take a taxi to get home from the shop.</li>
</ol></li>

<li>If necessary, complete the sentences with a, an or the.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>……… / a   / the</li>
<li>the / the</li>
<li>the / the</li>
<li>……… / a</li>
<li>………</li>
<li>……… / a</li>
<li>………</li>
<li>……… / the</li>
</ol></li>

<li>Correct the errors in these sentences.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>I like coffee with milk.</li>
<li>My brother is a mechanic.</li>
<li>Flowers are beautiful in spring.</li>
<li>What an elegant person.</li>
<li>Come on Sam. Go to bed right now.</li>
<li>My brother's ill in hospital.</li>
<li>We have dinner at 8 o'clock.</li>
<li>What do you say: the University of Cambridge or Cambridge
University?</li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org7498325" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org7498325">Unit 4</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org7498325">
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>Order these words to make correct sentences.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>She is a rich person.</li>
<li>This coffee tastes awful.</li>
<li>That music sounds nice.</li>
<li>There is a crazy man in the main building.</li>
<li>We are very happy to be here.</li>
<li>Those books are interesting.</li>
</ol></li>

<li value="3">Write sentences using the comparative of the adjective in brackets.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>London is bigger than Madrid.</li>
<li>The piramids are older than the Eiffel Tower.</li>
<li>Chinese is more difficult than English.</li>
<li>Woody Allen is thinner than Marlon Brando.</li>
<li>Leonardo DiCaprio is younger than Sean Connery.</li>
<li>Reading books is more interesting thon playing with video games.</li>
<li>A months holiday is better than a week's holiday.</li>
<li>Finland is colder than Spain.</li>
</ol></li>

<li>Complete the sentences with the superlative of the adjective in
brackets.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>The Petronas Twin Towers are the highest buildings in Malaysia.</li>
<li>The Nile is the longest river in Africa.</li>
<li>In your opinion, who is the best singer in the world?</li>
<li>Reading a good book is the most relaxing way to pass the time.</li>
<li>Who has the biggest fortune in the world?</li>
<li>This is one of the most economical cars I've ever driven.</li>
<li>This is the worst cold I've ever had.</li>
<li>It was the most beautiful dress I'd ever owned.</li>
</ol></li>

<li>Choose the correct word to complete the sentences.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>Jane is much taller than Jennifer.</li>
<li>My friend Peter is as old as me.</li>
<li>She likes the same things as I do.</li>
<li>Our house is farther from the station than yours.</li>
<li>Your shirt isn't as clean as mine.</li>
<li>Frank is the intelligent boy of the class.</li>
<li>Traditional food is better than fast food.</li>
<li>Italian is the easiest language I've ever learnt.</li>
</ol></li>

<li>Rewrite these sentences as in the example.
<ol class="org-ol">
<li>French is interesting to learn.</li>
<li>Mr Bean is funny to watch.</li>
<li>Spaghetti isn't difficult to cook.</li>
<li>These instructions are easy to understand.</li>
<li>His name is hard to pronounce.</li>
<li>These kinds of trees are unusual to find in this area.</li>
</ol></li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
